---
// src/pages/panel-upgrade-timeline.astro (example path)
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

const pageTitle = "How Long Does a Panel Upgrade Take in Las Vegas? | Timeline";
const pageDescription =
  "A detailed timeline of the electrical panel upgrade process in Las Vegas, including permit approval, installation day, and how long your power will be out.";
---

<Layout title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription}>
  <main class="bg-white text-gray-800">
    <!-- Page Header -->
    <section class="page-header-timeline text-white py-16">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold">
          How Long Does a Panel Upgrade Take?
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-gray-300 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          Understanding the project timeline, from the first call to the final
          inspection, helps you plan for the upgrade with confidence.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Main Content Area -->
    <section>
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16 xl:py-24">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
          <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none mb-12 text-gray-700">
            <p>
              One of the most common questions we hear is, “How long will my
              power be out?” While the actual hands-on installation is typically
              completed in a single day, the entire project has several phases.
              Here’s a clear breakdown of the timeline you can expect for a
              standard panel upgrade in Las Vegas.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Timeline Section -->
          <div class="space-y-8">
            <!-- Item 1 -->
            <div class="flex">
              <div class="flex flex-col items-center mr-6">
                <div
                  class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full timeline-item-dot flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold text-lg"
                >
                  1
                </div>
                <div
                  class="w-1 flex-grow timeline-item-connector border-l-2 border-dashed"
                >
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="flex-1">
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">
                  Phase 1: Consultation &amp; Permitting
                </h3>
                <p class="font-semibold text-gray-600 mt-1">
                  Duration: 1–3 Weeks
                </p>
                <p class="text-gray-700 mt-3">
                  This initial phase involves administrative work. After our
                  free consultation and your approval of the proposal, we submit
                  the permit application to Clark County or your city’s building
                  department. The time it takes for the permit to be approved
                  can vary depending on their current workload, but 1–3 weeks is
                  typical.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Item 2 -->
            <div class="flex">
              <div class="flex flex-col items-center mr-6">
                <div
                  class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full timeline-item-dot flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold text-lg"
                >
                  2
                </div>
                <div
                  class="w-1 flex-grow timeline-item-connector border-l-2 border-dashed"
                >
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="flex-1">
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">
                  Phase 2: Installation Day
                </h3>
                <p class="font-semibold text-gray-600 mt-1">
                  Duration: 6–10 Hours
                </p>
                <p class="text-gray-700 mt-3">
                  This is the main event. Once the permit is approved, we
                  schedule your installation. Our team will handle the entire
                  replacement on this day.
                </p>
                <div
                  class="mt-4 bg-yellow-100 border-l-4 border-yellow-500 text-yellow-800 p-4 rounded-md"
                >
                  <h4 class="font-bold">Power Outage Duration: 4–8 Hours</h4>
                  <p>
                    During the installation, your home’s power will be
                    completely shut off for safety. This typically lasts between
                    4 and 8 hours. We recommend planning ahead for this
                    disruption.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Item 3 -->
            <div class="flex">
              <div class="flex flex-col items-center mr-6">
                <div
                  class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full timeline-item-dot flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold text-lg"
                >
                  3
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="flex-1">
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">
                  Phase 3: City/County Inspection
                </h3>
                <p class="font-semibold text-gray-600 mt-1">
                  Duration: 1–3 Business Days Post-Installation
                </p>
                <p class="text-gray-700 mt-3">
                  After the installation is complete, we schedule the final
                  inspection with the city or county inspector. This usually
                  happens within a few business days. We coordinate this for
                  you. Once the inspector signs off on the work, the project is
                  officially complete.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- Final CTA -->
      <div
        class="mt-16 text-center bg-gray-800 text-white py-16 xl:py-24 rounded-lg shadow-xl"
      >
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-extrabold">Ready to Get Started?</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-gray-300 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          The first step is a simple, no-pressure consultation to assess your
          needs. Let’s get your project on the schedule.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-8">
          <a
            href="/company/company/contact-us/"
            class="bg-accent text-black font-bold py-3 px-8 rounded-full text-lg hover:bg-accent-dark transition-transform duration-300 inline-block transform hover:scale-105"
          >
            Schedule Your Free Consultation
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
<style>
  /* Accent utilities (scoped for this page) */
  .bg-accent {
    background-color: #f1b725;
  } /* amber-400 */
  .text-accent {
    color: #f1b725;
  }
  .border-accent {
    border-color: #f1b725;
  }
  .hover\:bg-accent-dark:hover {
    background-color: #f59e0b;
  } /* amber-500 */
  .ring-accent {
    --tw-ring-color: #f1b725;
  }

  /* Template-specific */
  .page-header-timeline {
    background-color: #064e3b;
  } /* green-900 */
  .timeline-item-dot {
    background-color: #10b981;
  } /* emerald-500 */
  .timeline-item-connector {
    border-color: #6ee7b7;
  } /* emerald-300 */
</style>
